article.headline: Old Dominion 80, Winston-Salem 50
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Gerald Lee scored 18 points to lead Old Dominion in an 80-50 win against Winston-Salem State on Tuesday night. Ben Finney added 13 points and Darius James had 11 for the Monarchs (8-3), who shot 49.1 percent from the field (28 of 57). James hit 3 of 5 shots from beyond the arc, while Finney went 2-for-3. Both Lee and James were perfect from the free-throw line, going 4-for-4 and 2-for-2, respectively. Brian Fisher scored 15 points to lead the Rams (3-8), who shot just 25.4 percent (16 of 63). After trailing 4-3 less than one minute into the game, the Monarchs went on a 17-0 run. Old Dominion outscored Winston-Salem State 40-25 in both halves.
